      <h2 id="why-email-marketing-works">Why Email Marketing Works for HVAC Companies</h2>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Email marketing delivers a 4200% ROI for service businesses, making it one of the most cost-effective customer retention tools available. For HVAC companies, email excels because:</p>

        <p><strong>Maintenance scheduling drives predictable revenue.</strong> The average residential HVAC system needs maintenance twice yearly (spring and fall), creating natural touchpoints for email campaigns. Companies using automated maintenance reminders report 60-70% higher maintenance contract renewal rates.</p>

        <p><strong>Seasonal demand creates campaign opportunities.</strong> HVAC businesses see 40% of annual revenue during peak summer and winter months. Strategic pre-season emails can capture this demand before competitors.</p>

        <p><strong>Emergency services have high conversion rates.</strong> When a system fails, customers often research contractors online first. Staying visible through regular emails increases the likelihood they'll call you during emergencies.</p>

        <p>The numbers prove email's effectiveness: HVAC companies report average email open rates of 25-30%, click rates of 3-5%, and conversion rates of 2-4% for maintenance scheduling campaigns.</p>
      </div>

