      <h2 id="customer-reactivation-sequences">Customer Reactivation Sequences</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Customer reactivation campaigns target customers who haven't used your services in 12-18 months. These sequences typically achieve 8-12% response rates and can recover 15-20% of dormant customers.</p>

        <p>A typical reactivation sequence includes 3-4 emails sent over 6 weeks:</p>

        <p><strong>Email 1 (Week 1): "We miss you"</strong> - Acknowledge the gap in service, offer a special returning customer discount (typically 10-15%), and highlight any new services you've added.</p>

        <p><strong>Email 2 (Week 3): "Here's what's new"</strong> - Share company updates, new technology, team additions, or service improvements. Include customer testimonials from recent work.</p>

        <p><strong>Email 3 (Week 5): "Last chance offer"</strong> - Present a time-sensitive incentive (expires in 2 weeks) and make booking as easy as possible with direct scheduling links.</p>

        <p><strong>Email 4 (Week 6): "We're here when you need us"</strong> - Soft close emphasizing your continued availability for emergency service, with no sales pressure.</p>

        <p>Reactivation campaigns work best when personalized with specific service history. For example, "We last serviced your Carrier furnace in March 2024" performs better than generic messaging.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="email-templates-examples">Proven Email Templates</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Here are proven email templates that consistently drive bookings for HVAC companies:</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Template 1: Maintenance Reminder</h3>
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border rounded-lg p-4 my-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-2">Subject: Sarah, Your Furnace Service is Due (Save 15%)</p>
        <div class="text-sm text-blue-700">
          <p>Hi Sarah,</p>
          <p class="my-2">Our records show we last serviced your Lennox furnace on March 15, 2025. With winter approaching, it's time for your annual heating system maintenance.</p>
          <p class="my-2">Book by October 31st and save 15% on service (reg. $149, now $126).</p>
          <p class="my-2"><strong>What's Included:</strong><br>
          ✓ 28-point safety inspection<br>
          ✓ Filter replacement<br>
          ✓ Efficiency optimization<br>
          ✓ 1-year service warranty</p>
          <p class="my-2"><strong>[Schedule Online]</strong> or call (555) 123-4567</p>
          <p>Thanks,<br>Mike Johnson<br>ABC Heating & Air</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Template 2: Seasonal Promotion</h3>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border rounded-lg p-4 my-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-green-800 mb-2">Subject: Beat the Summer Rush - AC Tune-up Special</p>
        <div class="text-sm text-green-700">
          <p>Hi [First Name],</p>
          <p class="my-2">Don't wait for the first 90-degree day! Smart homeowners schedule AC maintenance in April before the summer rush begins.</p>
          <p class="my-2"><strong>April Special: $99 AC Tune-up</strong> (regular $149)<br>
          Includes cleaning, calibration, and peace of mind for summer.</p>
          <p class="my-2"><strong>Why schedule early?</strong><br>
          • Avoid emergency service fees<br>
          • Priority scheduling when you need us<br>
          • 20% longer equipment life<br>
          • Lower energy bills all summer</p>
          <p class="my-2">Limited slots available. <strong>[Book Now]</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Template 3: Emergency Weather Alert</h3>
      <div class="bg-red-50 border rounded-lg p-4 my-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-red-800 mb-2">Subject: Freeze Warning Tonight - Protect Your Pipes!</p>
        <div class="text-sm text-red-700">
          <p>URGENT: Temperatures dropping to 18°F tonight in [City Name]</p>
          <p class="my-2"><strong>Protect your home:</strong><br>
          ✓ Let faucets drip slightly<br>
          ✓ Open cabinet doors under sinks<br>
          ✓ Set thermostat to 68°F minimum<br>
          ✓ Check that your furnace is running</p>
          <p class="my-2">If your heat stops working, call our emergency line: <strong>(555) 123-4567</strong></p>
          <p class="my-2">We're standing by 24/7.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>These templates achieve higher open and click rates because they provide immediate value, use specific details, and include clear calls-to-action. Customize them with your branding, pricing, and local details for best results.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="tracking-email-performance">Tracking Email Performance</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Successful HVAC email campaigns require tracking key metrics beyond basic open and click rates. Here are the KPIs that matter most:</p>

        <p><strong>Revenue per email</strong> measures total campaign value divided by emails sent. Top-performing HVAC campaigns generate $3-8 per email sent. Calculate this by tracking bookings and average job values generated from each campaign.</p>

        <p><strong>Booking conversion rate</strong> tracks how many email recipients actually schedule services. Maintenance campaigns typically convert 8-15%, while promotional campaigns convert 3-8%.</p>

        <p><strong>List growth rate</strong> shows how quickly you're building your email database. Healthy HVAC companies grow their lists by 3-5% monthly through service completions, website signups, and referrals.</p>

        <p><strong>Unsubscribe rate</strong> should stay under 2% per campaign. Higher rates indicate poor targeting, too-frequent sending, or irrelevant content.</p>

        <p>Use <a href="https://partners.callrail.com/ut5waejxy35l" rel="sponsored nofollow" target="_blank">call tracking numbers</a> in emails to measure phone bookings generated by campaigns. This captures the full ROI since many customers prefer calling over online scheduling.</p>
      </div>

