        <p>The most successful HVAC email campaigns integrate seamlessly with field service software to automate customer communication based on actual service data.</p>

        <p><strong><a href="https://go.getjobber.com/vcuhehgs796s" rel="sponsored nofollow" target="_blank">Jobber's email features</a></strong> automatically trigger maintenance reminders based on your service intervals. Set up annual maintenance for each customer type, and Jobber sends personalized emails 30 days before scheduled service. Pricing starts at $49/month for teams up to 3 users.</p>

        <p><strong><a href="https://housecallpro.partnerlinks.io/auy5xcz257sw" rel="sponsored nofollow" target="_blank">HousecallPro</a></strong> offers more advanced segmentation, letting you target customers by equipment brand, service history, or property value. Their email templates include equipment photos and service history details pulled directly from your database. Plans start at $59/month.</p>

        <p>Both platforms sync with popular email marketing tools if you need advanced features like A/B testing or detailed analytics. This hybrid approach lets you use CRM data for targeting while leveraging dedicated email platform features for campaign optimization.</p>

        <p>For companies using <a href="/hvac/pricing/servicetitan-pricing">ServiceTitan</a>, email integration requires third-party tools like Mailchimp or Constant Contact, adding $20-50/month to your software costs but providing more sophisticated automation capabilities.</p>
