      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h3>Getting Started With HVAC Email Marketing</h3>
        <p>Begin with these three foundational campaigns that generate immediate results:</p>
        
        <p><strong>1. Automated maintenance reminders</strong> for existing customers based on their last service date. Set these up in your CRM to trigger 30 days before recommended service intervals.</p>

        <p><strong>2. Seasonal tune-up campaigns</strong> sent 6-8 weeks before peak seasons. Focus on preventing breakdowns rather than selling new equipment.</p>

        <p><strong>3. Post-service follow-up emails</strong> sent 3-5 days after job completion, asking for reviews and offering maintenance plan enrollment.</p>

        <p>These three campaigns alone typically generate 15-25% more repeat business within 90 days of implementation. As you build confidence and see results, expand into reactivation sequences and promotional campaigns.</p>

        <p>Email marketing success for HVAC companies comes down to consistency, personalization, and timing. Start simple, track your results, and gradually expand your campaigns as you see ROI from your initial efforts.</p>
